                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2002-10-30</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I am 16 years old and I play on my high schools varsity baseball team. I feel this book has helped my outlook on my sports career, because some of his quotes are so true. Everytime I wake up at 5:30 to weightlift before school I remind myself "The harder you work, the harder it is to surrender." Just reading this book made me realize what it really takes to be #1. You can't be a sissy, you have to work for what you want. Any athlete who needs something to motivate them should read this book.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">It pays to be tough Leader when achieving something great</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
